---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QuickSummary from '../components/QuickSummary.astro';
---

<Layout title="Stores" description="In-game store priorities and real money value guide for Last War: Survival.">
  <h1>Stores</h1>

  <QuickSummary>
    <p>Always spend on things that directly upgrade your <strong>main squad</strong> first. Everything else is secondary until that squad is strong.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>In-Game Store Priorities (Mid-Game)</h2>

  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Store</th><th>Priority Buys</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Alliance Store</strong></td>
          <td>Hero shards for your main squad heroes, Skill Medals, Gear materials. Avoid cosmetic items early.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Black Market</strong></td>
          <td>Universal shards, high-value gear components, and recruitment tickets when the price is good.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Season Shop</strong></td>
          <td>Season-exclusive shards and materials for your main type. Prioritize what helps your current squad.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>VIP / Monthly Rewards</strong></td>
          <td>Consistent daily/weekly resources. Very efficient if you’re active.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Real Money Value Guide (Honest)</h2>
  <p class="text-sm">For most new and mid-game players, the best value is usually:</p>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 text-sm space-y-1 mt-2">
    <li><strong>Monthly Card</strong> — Steady resources every day with very little spending.</li>
    <li><strong>Battle Pass</strong> — Excellent value if you play regularly and complete the missions.</li>
    <li><strong>VIP levels</strong> (early ones) — Good permanent bonuses.</li>
  </ol>

  <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">Big one-time packs are generally poor value compared to consistent small spending. The game is very playable as a disciplined low spender or even F2P if you focus on one squad and events.</p>
</Layout>